.TH "TEXTTRACKCUE.ENTER_EVENT" "3JS" "July 20, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TextTrackCue.enter_event \- TextTrackCue: enter event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]enter\f[B]\f[R] event fires when a cue becomes active.
In the case of subtitles or a caption this is when it displays over the
media.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqenter\(dq, (event) => { })

onenter = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R] with no added properties.
.SH EXAMPLE
In the following example, \f[CR]cue\f[R] prints to the console when it
is the active cue.
.IP
.EX
cue.addEventListener(\(dqenter\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(\(dqCue 1 has displayed\(dq);
});
.EE
